{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Clockwork (Gujarati et al. 2020) leverages the predictable performance of the DNNs, considers the SLO guarantees on the server, and maps requests to the desired model, but does not utilize DNN adaptation.",
    "Inferline (Crankshaw et al. 2020), Llama (Romero et al. 2021b), and FA2 (Razavi et al. 2022) optimize the serving of complex DNN pipelines.",
    "INFaas (Romero et al. 2021a) automates the hardware and model-variant selection and deployment through managed services.",
    "Model-Switching (Zhang et al. 2020a) proposes to scale DNNs (up and down) instead of scaling resources in the case of fluctuating workload.",
    "None of these cloud-based solutions consider the impact of the dynamic edge network on the end-to-end latency."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
